Let me ask you first a question pertaining to you. 
you meet people and tell them what you do, what do

02:15.638 --> 02:19.603
they think? I mean, do they think astronomers are 
sponging off productive elements, or do they

02:19.623 --> 02:25.932
think it's a neat job? I have very seldom had a 
reaction such as you describe. Usually it's, oh,

02:30.038 --> 02:32.000
how interesting. And when I tell them about 
Hubble, they say, oh, well, what went wrong? Or,

02:38.670 --> 02:39.471
oh, yeah. But there's clearly a lot of interest in 
astronomy as astronomy. You know, people I've

02:45.558 --> 03:01.162
talked to on the planes, I'll get a picture or an 
article, they'll send me in the mail, you know,

02:45.558 --> 03:01.162
some insurance executive or what have you will 
