07:48.584 --> 07:52.011
money. in the sense that you need access to a 
computer primarily. Most of the interesting

07:58.984 --> 08:05.111
research is being done by massaging, you know, 
running computer programs these days. Well, I

08:05.191 --> 08:13.139
mean, I'm talking particularly here about are you 
still encouraging graduate students to enter the

08:05.191 --> 08:13.139
field or not? I encourage people to enter fields 
that they have interest in. I don't I've never, you

08:17.793 --> 08:29.887
know, either encouraged or discouraged a student 
from going into a particular area of astronomy or

08:17.793 --> 08:29.887
into astronomy itself based on whether or not 
they'll find a job at the end of it. I think that if

08:29.907 --> 08:33.891
you're good, there'll be a job. And the only way to 
find out if you're good is to try it and see.

